  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Lynn Women&apos;s Anti-Slavery Society has felt sufficiently encouraged by Mrs. Maria Weston Chapman and her friends to proceed with its plans for a fair. The children&apos;s hose, mittens, and toys sell the best in Lynn. Eliza Boyce writes: &quot;Were it not for a few individuals I believe the society would long before this have disbanded.&quot; She complains of a spirit of indifference and apathy. She invites Maria W. Chapman and Mrs. Lydia Maria Child to address the Lynn Women&apos;s Anti-Slavery Society.</subfield>
